<p>I don't know if i'd call the Critic a &quot;leader&quot; in the conventional sense. He oversees the particular cell the story is based around, but his job isn't to lead as much as it is to, as the name implies, <em>criticize</em>. The codenames, I figure, arose out of a sort of &quot;death of the artist&quot; mentality - the individual producing the work is irrelevant in comparison to the work itself, so they just take on names that get passed down from person to person as people retire, get captured, etc.</p>

							</div>

								
					
