					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kinchtheknifeblade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1345012); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1345012&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610250560" alt="kinchtheknifeblade" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1345012)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kinchtheknifeblade" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1345012); return false;" >kinchtheknifeblade</a></span> <span class="odate time_1339434890 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">11 Jun 2012 17:14</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1477202">
									

<p>I really, really like the idea of (at least part of) AWCY? being led by a community college art prof codenamed The Critic. It meshes surprisingly well with my headcanon. I like that what they're doing is ALMOST a workshop (something I've been wishing to explore in an SCP but haven't yet).</p>
<p>I was ready to downvote this for the trashing of various (deleted) SCPs while glorifying one of your own, but you made some really, really good points. I'm impressed with this.</p>

							</div>

								
					
